<Content>Excellent hotel, can't go wrong We stayed eary November in the hotel. We took a bus from the airport to the hotel, for only 5E each. The drop-off in Plaza Catalunya was a simple three blocks away. The hotel is very modern, very clean, and very cozy. The rooms have a decent size, the bed is very comfortable, and the bathroom has all the amenities you could need.The front desk service is nice enough (at least to Barcelona standards), although not terribly helpful regarding the area.One drawback is that internet access is very expensive. As for the area, go to las Ramblas and take leisurely strolls around the area. The Carrefur Express market is great to stock up, and we love Pan  Company for a quick snack (Subway with a Spanish flare). Note that on Sunday almost everyting is closed (which didn't make a lot of sense!).Overall, the NH Calderon is an excellent option and I would return to it (this was our second stay there). 
