<Content>Good 4* hotel Myself and three friends stayed at the Calderon for three nights and found it excellent. The staff were helpful and polite and the facilities were more than adequate. The pool area on the roof isn't huge but it's clean with fantastic views and the pool itself provides great respite from the heat. The location is fab - right next to the shopping area and La Rambla. You can also see the Gaudi apartments, the Catherdral and the Gaudi Church from the roof top. It's close the the metro station and there are plenty of bars and restaurants nearby. The only niggle was the breakfast - while it is a lovely selection of food and drink beautifully presented unless you completely stuff yourself you feel slightly ripped off at the 17.50 euro charge every morning! However, we would definitely return to the Calderon, especially at just 110 euro per night. 
