<Content>Great location I agree with the July 13, 2004 visitor. I have been to Barcelona five times and stayed here on my last visit in June 2004. The location is the best thing about the hotel. It is a great value for a chain-type hotel if you get a deal on the room rates. We had a triple so our room was quite large. The bathroom was huge and the room was very quiet. We didn't eat here, but ate at the numerous places nearby. It is close to transit-bus, and metro, and near the airport bus stop. There is an internet cafe nearby, a high end convenience-type store open late hours across the street, and major shopping nearby. Don't expect much for service, and you won't be disappointed. For first time visitors, I would recommend it as it is in a safe area with lots of places to eat nearby and close to many transit options. Also of major importance during the summer is the superb air conditioning. The roof-top pool offers great vistas of the city. 
