<Content>Clean, Modern Hotel, Good Location Searched endless sites trying to find a suitable hotel for my stay first stay in Barcelona and plummed for this one after being messed around by Rivoli Ramblas. What I did realise was that whats good for some is not for others. My opinion of the Calderon was that it was a clean, comfortable and modern hotel, well located for sightseeing and shopping. Pass.de Gracia is the main shopping district and is one block away. The tube stations of Pass.de Gracia and Placa Catalunya are 5 min walks. The airport train stops at the latter and only costs 2.25 EUROS. This hotel seems to be run by a chain similar to the Marriot or Holiday Inn. We stayed on a Room Only basis for 110 Euros which was a discounted rate. The room was well decorated with Dark Wood and black marble the main features and a large marble bathroom. It was spotlessly clean with TV, remote radio which played music throughout room and into bathroom. If you can get a good rate you cant go wrong with this obvious 4 star hotel. Only negative was that out of the 3 reception staff we spoke to only one was smiling. The others were not rude or unhelpful just seemed miserable. This was the only negative point and relatively minor as we didnt need to rely on them at all. 
